1
00:00:07,458 --> 00:00:09,166
Katara: WATER...

2
00:00:09,208 --> 00:00:11,041
EARTH...

3
00:00:11,083 --> 00:00:13,166
FIRE...

4
00:00:13,208 --> 00:00:15,709
AIR.

5
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:17,000
LONG AGO...

6
00:00:17,041 --> 00:00:19,041
THE FOUR NATIONS LIVED
TOGETHER IN HARMONY.

7
00:00:19,083 --> 00:00:24,041
THEN EVERYTHING CHANGED
WHEN THE FIRE NATION ATTACKED.

8
00:00:24,083 --> 00:00:28,041
ONLY THE AVATAR,
MASTER OF ALL FOUR ELEMENTS
COULD STOP THEM.

9
00:00:28,083 --> 00:00:29,834
BUT WHEN THE WORLD
NEEDED HIM MOST

10
00:00:29,875 --> 00:00:32,041
HE VANISHED.

11
00:00:32,083 --> 00:00:35,750
100 YEARS PASSED, AND MY BROTHER
AND I DISCOVERED THE NEW AVATAR

12
00:00:35,792 --> 00:00:37,542
AN AIRBENDER NAMED AANG.

13
00:00:37,583 --> 00:00:39,959
AND ALTHOUGH HIS AIRBENDING
SKILLS WERE GREAT

14
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,250
HE HAS A LOT TO LEARN BEFORE
HE'S READY TO SAVE ANYONE.

15
00:00:43,291 --> 00:00:47,375
BUT I BELIEVE AANG
CAN SAVE THE WORLD.

16
00:00:47,417 --> 00:00:49,417
♪

17
00:00:56,166 --> 00:00:58,250
Aang: BLENDING IN IS BETTER
THAN HIDING OUT.

18
00:00:58,291 --> 00:01:02,375
IF WE GET FIRE NATION DISGUISES,
WE'LL BE JUST AS SAFE AS
WE WOULD BE HIDING IN A CAVE.

19
00:01:02,417 --> 00:01:04,375
YOU HAVE NO RIGHT
TO JUDGE ME, UNCLE.

20
00:01:04,417 --> 00:01:08,542
I DID WHAT I HAD TO DO
IN BA SING SE, AND YOU WERE
A FOOL FOR NOT JOINING ME.

21
00:01:11,917 --> 00:01:14,959
I SEE YOU FAVOR
THE WHITE LOTUS GAMBIT.

22
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:19,000
NOT MANY STILL CLING
TO THE ANCIENT WAYS.

23
00:01:19,041 --> 00:01:21,667
THOSE WHO DO CAN ALWAYS
FIND A FRIEND.

24
00:01:30,834 --> 00:01:34,500
Katara: WOW, THIS IS AMAZING
TO WATCH.

25
00:01:34,542 --> 00:01:37,375
KIND OF MAKES YOU REALIZE
HOW INSIGNIFICANT WE ARE.

26
00:01:37,417 --> 00:01:41,208
EH, YOU'VE SEEN NOTHING ONCE,
YOU'VE SEEN IT 1,000 TIMES.

27
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:43,250
[ALL GASPING]

28
00:01:43,291 --> 00:01:44,375
Sokka: OH, MAN.

29
00:01:44,417 --> 00:01:46,083
YOU'VE NEVER NOT SEEN
ANYTHING LIKE THIS.

30
00:01:51,625 --> 00:01:53,125
[EXPLOSION]

31
00:01:59,667 --> 00:02:04,291
Katara: THE FIRE IS GONNA
DESTROY THAT TOWN.

32
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:05,542
Aang: NOT IF WE CAN STOP IT.

33
00:02:05,583 --> 00:02:08,542
[GROWLING]

34
00:02:08,583 --> 00:02:10,166
THERE'S A CREEK OVER HERE.

35
00:02:10,208 --> 00:02:12,291
I'LL BEND THE WATER
ON TO THE FIRE.

36
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:15,125
TOPH, LET'S MAKE A TRENCH
TO KEEP THE FIRE
FROM COMING ANY CLOSER.

37
00:02:16,834 --> 00:02:17,709
WHAT SHOULD I DO?

38
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:19,083
[MOMO SQUAWKING]

39
00:02:19,125 --> 00:02:20,709
KEEP AN EYE ON MOMO.

40
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:24,208
SO WHAT, I'M JUST
A LEMUR-SITTER?

41
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:25,291
THERE, THERE.

42
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:26,125
FEEL BETTER?

43
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:39,750
[GASPING]

44
00:03:02,208 --> 00:03:05,583
SOKKA, STAND CLEAR.

45
00:03:05,625 --> 00:03:07,458
RIGHT, STAND CLEAR.

46
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:08,333
GOT IT.

47
00:03:08,375 --> 00:03:11,208
[INHALING]

48
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:13,125
[GASPING]

49
00:03:18,875 --> 00:03:20,000
GOOD WORK, EVERYBODY.

50
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:25,583
[MOMO WARBLING]

51
00:03:37,041 --> 00:03:37,917
[GASPING]

52
00:03:37,959 --> 00:03:39,792
[MAKING EATING NOISES]

53
00:03:39,834 --> 00:03:40,917
Man: LOOK AT YOU.

54
00:03:40,959 --> 00:03:43,583
YOU'RE JUST A FAT,
DISGUSTING OLD MAN.

55
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:46,125
YOU DO NOTHING, YOU SAY NOTHING.

56
00:03:46,166 --> 00:03:49,750
YOU JUST EAT AND ROLL AROUND
IN YOUR OWN FILTH LIKE A PIG.

57
00:03:49,792 --> 00:03:50,959
YOU'RE A DISGRACE.

58
00:04:05,917 --> 00:04:10,667
THESE PEOPLE HAVE NO IDEA
HOW CLOSE THEY WERE
TO GETTING TOASTED LAST NIGHT.

59
00:04:10,709 --> 00:04:13,208
YEAH, THE WORST THING
ABOUT BEING IN DISGUISE

60
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:15,625
IS WE DON'T GET
THE HERO WORSHIP ANYMORE.

61
00:04:15,667 --> 00:04:17,250
I MISS THE LOVE.

62
00:04:17,291 --> 00:04:20,125
BOO-HOO, POOR HEROES.

63
00:04:20,166 --> 00:04:21,875
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

64
00:04:21,917 --> 00:04:24,208
YOU HAVEN'T EVEN TOUCHED
YOUR SMOKED SEA SLUG.

65
00:04:24,250 --> 00:04:27,250
IT'S JUST, ALL YOU GUYS CAN DO
THIS AWESOME BENDING STUFF

66
00:04:27,291 --> 00:04:31,291
LIKE PUTTING OUT FOREST FIRES,
AND FLYING AROUND, AND MAKING
OTHER STUFF FLY AROUND.

67
00:04:32,542 --> 00:04:34,375
I CAN'T FLY AROUND, OK?

68
00:04:34,417 --> 00:04:36,625
I CAN'T DO ANYTHING.

69
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:38,625
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

70
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:40,792
NO ONE CAN READ A MAP LIKE YOU.

71
00:04:40,834 --> 00:04:42,625
I CAN'T READ AT ALL.

72
00:04:42,667 --> 00:04:45,125
YEAH, AND WHO KEEPS US LAUGHING
WITH SARCASTIC COMMENTS
ALL THE TIME?

73
00:04:45,166 --> 00:04:48,083
I MEAN,
LOOK AT KATARA'S HAIR, RIGHT?

74
00:04:48,125 --> 00:04:49,291
WHAT'S UP WITH THAT?

75
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:50,125
WHAT?

76
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:51,792
WHAT'S WRONG WITH MY HAIR?

77
00:04:51,834 --> 00:04:53,542
NOTHING, I WAS JUST TRYING TO...

78
00:04:53,583 --> 00:04:56,583
Sokka: LOOK, I APPRECIATE
THE EFFORT, BUT THE FACT IS

79
00:04:56,625 --> 00:05:01,417
EACH OF YOU IS SO AMAZING
AND SO SPECIAL, AND I'M NOT.

80
00:05:02,917 --> 00:05:05,208
I'M JUST THE GUY
IN THE GROUP WHO'S REGULAR.

81
00:05:09,041 --> 00:05:13,041
I'M SORRY YOU'RE FEELING
SO DOWN, BUT I HOPE YOU KNOW
NONE OF US SEE YOU THAT WAY.

82
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:17,458
I KNOW SOMETHING THAT'S GONNA
MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER.

83
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,166
YOU DO?

84
00:05:19,208 --> 00:05:21,542
SHOPPING.

85
00:05:21,583 --> 00:05:25,125
MAYBE A LITTLE SOMETHING
TO REINVIGORATE MY BATTLING.

86
00:05:26,041 --> 00:05:27,500
HEY, HOW ABOUT THESE?

87
00:05:27,542 --> 00:05:29,792
HI-YA!

88
00:05:29,834 --> 00:05:31,208
"SMACK-A-DACKA-DOO!"

89
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:34,959
[GRUNTING...]

90
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,750
Aang: WHAT DO YOU THINK?

91
00:05:36,792 --> 00:05:40,875
PRETTY SLICK, HUH?

92
00:05:40,917 --> 00:05:43,291
ALL I NEED TO COMPLETE
THE OUTFIT IS A WIND SWORD.

93
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:44,667
WHAT'S A WIND SWORD?

94
00:05:44,709 --> 00:05:46,417
IT'S WHERE I GET A SWORD HANDLE

95
00:05:46,458 --> 00:05:49,458
AND THEN I JUST SWING
THIS AROUND AND BEND AIR OUT
LIKE A BLADE.

96
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:52,625
[MAKING WHOOSHING SOUND]

97
00:05:52,667 --> 00:05:54,750
YEAH, NICE.

98
00:05:54,792 --> 00:05:57,625
[WHIMPERING]

99
00:05:57,667 --> 00:05:59,250
I'LL JUST STICK TO WHAT I GOT.

100
00:06:04,208 --> 00:06:07,875
[GROANING]

101
00:06:07,917 --> 00:06:09,208
[GRUNTING]

102
00:06:23,959 --> 00:06:26,041
OOH.

103
00:06:26,083 --> 00:06:28,583
THAT'S WHAT SOKKA'S
TALKING ABOUT.

104
00:06:28,625 --> 00:06:29,792
Man: YOU HAVE A GOOD EYE.

105
00:06:29,834 --> 00:06:31,875
THAT'S AN ORIGINAL FROM PIANDAO

106
00:06:31,917 --> 00:06:34,917
THE GREATEST SWORD MASTER
AND SWORD MAKER
IN FIRE NATION HISTORY.

107
00:06:34,959 --> 00:06:37,625
HE LIVES IN THE BIG CASTLE
UP THE ROAD FROM HERE.

108
00:06:37,667 --> 00:06:39,875
THAT'S IT.

109
00:06:39,917 --> 00:06:41,750
THAT'S WHAT YOU NEEDED
ALL ALONG, SOKKA.

110
00:06:41,792 --> 00:06:42,625
A SWORD?

111
00:06:42,667 --> 00:06:43,583
NOT THE SWORD.

112
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:45,667
A MASTER.

113
00:06:45,709 --> 00:06:47,834
WE'VE ALL HAD MASTERS
TO HELP US GET BETTER.

114
00:06:47,875 --> 00:06:49,750
YOU SHOULD SEE IF YOU
CAN STUDY WITH PIANDAO.

115
00:06:49,792 --> 00:06:51,458
THAT'S A GREAT IDEA.

116
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:53,959
I COULD'VE NEVER GOTTEN TO WHERE
I AM WITHOUT MASTER PAKKU.

117
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,834
EVERYONE NEEDS A TEACHER.

118
00:06:55,875 --> 00:06:58,083
I LEARNED FROM BADGER MOLES.

119
00:06:58,125 --> 00:07:00,375
THEY DON'T TALK,
BUT THEY'RE STILL GOOD TEACHERS.

120
00:07:00,417 --> 00:07:03,375
IT WOULD BE NICE TO BE
A MASTER SWORDFIGHTER.

121
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:06,667
ALL RIGHT, I'LL TALK TO HIM.

122
00:07:13,625 --> 00:07:18,041
[GRUNTING...]

123
00:07:31,458 --> 00:07:32,291
[GASPING]

124
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:35,125
CAN I HELP YOU?

125
00:07:35,166 --> 00:07:37,166
I'VE COME TO TRAIN
WITH THE MASTER.

126
00:07:37,208 --> 00:07:40,041
YOU SHOULD KNOW THE MASTER
TURNS ALMOST EVERYONE AWAY.

127
00:07:41,417 --> 00:07:42,875
WHAT DID YOU BRING HIM
TO PROVE YOUR WORTH?

128
00:07:42,917 --> 00:07:46,250
WELL, UH...

129
00:07:46,291 --> 00:07:47,500
RIGHT.

130
00:07:47,542 --> 00:07:49,083
LET'S GET THIS OVER WITH.

131
00:08:01,041 --> 00:08:04,792
MASTER, MY NAME IS SOKKA,
AND I WISH TO BE INSTRUCTED
IN THE WAY OF THE SWORD.

132
00:08:04,834 --> 00:08:06,583
Piandao: SOKKA.

133
00:08:06,625 --> 00:08:08,375
THAT'S AN UNUSUAL NAME.

134
00:08:08,417 --> 00:08:10,000
OH, UH, REALLY?

135
00:08:10,041 --> 00:08:12,417
UH, WHERE I COME FROM,
THE FIRE NATION COLONIES

136
00:08:12,458 --> 00:08:15,917
IT'S A PRETTY NORMAL NAME,
FOR FIRE NATION COLONIALS.

137
00:08:15,959 --> 00:08:17,875
Piandao: LET ME GUESS.

138
00:08:17,917 --> 00:08:20,500
YOU'VE COME HUNDREDS OF MILES
FROM YOUR LITTLE VILLAGE

139
00:08:20,542 --> 00:08:23,333
WHERE YOU'RE THE BEST
SWORDSMAN IN TOWN

140
00:08:23,375 --> 00:08:26,625
AND YOU THINK YOU DESERVE
TO LEARN FROM THE MASTER.

141
00:08:26,667 --> 00:08:28,959
WELL, ACTUALLY, I'VE BEEN
ALL OVER THE WORLD.

142
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,458
Piandao: YEP, HERE WE GO.

143
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:35,542
AND I KNOW ONE THING FOR SURE:
I HAVE A LOT TO LEARN.

144
00:08:35,583 --> 00:08:38,959
YOU'RE NOT DOING A VERY GOOD JOB
OF SELLING YOURSELF.

145
00:08:39,667 --> 00:08:41,500
I KNOW.

146
00:08:41,542 --> 00:08:44,166
YOUR BUTLER TOLD ME
THAT WHEN I MET YOU,
I WOULD HAVE TO PROVE MY WORTH

147
00:08:44,208 --> 00:08:46,834
BUT THE TRUTH IS,
I DON'T KNOW IF I AM WORTHY.

148
00:08:46,875 --> 00:08:49,834
HM, I SEE.

149
00:08:49,875 --> 00:08:55,125
WELL, THEN, LET'S FIND OUT
TOGETHER HOW WORTHY YOU ARE.

150
00:08:56,959 --> 00:08:59,083
I WILL TRAIN YOU.

151
00:09:04,208 --> 00:09:09,667
THE FIRST THING YOU MUST LEARN
IS THAT YOUR WEAPON
IS AN EXTENSION OF YOURSELF.

152
00:09:09,709 --> 00:09:12,250
YOU MUST THINK OF IT AS
ANOTHER PART OF YOUR OWN BODY.

153
00:09:13,875 --> 00:09:16,041
LIKE A SECOND HEAD.

154
00:09:16,083 --> 00:09:21,208
WELL, MORE LIKE
AN EXTRA-LONG, REALLY SHARP ARM.

155
00:09:21,250 --> 00:09:25,250
THE SWORD IS A SIMPLE TOOL,
BUT IN THE HANDS OF A MASTER

156
00:09:25,291 --> 00:09:30,834
IT BECOMES THE MOST VERSATILE
OF WEAPONS, AND JUST AS
THE IMAGINATION IS LIMITLESS

157
00:09:30,875 --> 00:09:33,625
SO TOO ARE THE POSSIBILITIES
OF THE SWORD.

158
00:09:35,291 --> 00:09:38,208
Aang: WHAT SHOULD WE DO TODAY?

159
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,542
I'M TAPPED OUT.

160
00:09:39,583 --> 00:09:41,417
I ALREADY PICKED MY TOES, TWICE.

161
00:09:41,458 --> 00:09:43,792
TWICE?

162
00:09:43,834 --> 00:09:48,792
THE FIRST TIME WAS FOR CLEANING,
BUT THE SECOND TIME'S JUST FOR
THE SWEET PICKING SENSATION.

163
00:09:48,834 --> 00:09:50,500
SOKKA'S BEEN IN CHARGE
OF THE SCHEDULE.

164
00:09:50,542 --> 00:09:52,083
I'M NOT SURE
WHAT WE SHOULD BE DOING.

165
00:09:52,125 --> 00:09:55,333
PLUS, IT'S SO HOT TODAY.

166
00:09:55,375 --> 00:09:56,959
HOW HOT IS IT?

167
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:57,750
I DON'T KNOW.

168
00:09:57,792 --> 00:09:59,417
REAL HOT?

169
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:04,875
IT'S SO HOT, IT'S SO HOT,
MOMO IS SHEDDING LIKE APPA.

170
00:10:05,583 --> 00:10:09,250
HUH, HUH?

171
00:10:09,291 --> 00:10:11,875
I GUESS THE JOKES
DON'T RUN IN THE FAMILY.

172
00:10:11,917 --> 00:10:14,500
Katara: OH, EVERYONE'S A CRITIC.

173
00:10:14,542 --> 00:10:15,625
[APPA GROWLING]

174
00:10:15,667 --> 00:10:18,625
[GRUNTING]

175
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:31,375
THE WARRIOR PRACTICES
A VARIETY OF ARTS TO KEEP
HIS MIND SHARP AND FLUID.

176
00:10:31,417 --> 00:10:33,750
THE FIRST YOU WILL LEARN
IS CALLIGRAPHY.

177
00:10:33,792 --> 00:10:36,333
WRITE YOUR NAME.

178
00:10:36,375 --> 00:10:39,333
WRITING MY NAME WILL MAKE ME
A BETTER SWORDSMAN?

179
00:10:39,375 --> 00:10:43,917
WHEN YOU WRITE YOUR NAME,
YOU STAMP THE PAPER
WITH YOUR IDENTITY.

180
00:10:43,959 --> 00:10:47,750
YOU MUST LEARN TO USE YOUR SWORD
TO STAMP YOUR IDENTITY
ON A BATTLEFIELD.

181
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:56,250
REMEMBER, YOU CANNOT TAKE BACK
A STROKE OF THE BRUSH,
OR A STROKE OF THE SWORD.

182
00:11:00,834 --> 00:11:03,750
YOU ARE GETTING INK
ON YOUR FACE.

183
00:11:03,792 --> 00:11:05,583
I AM?

184
00:11:05,625 --> 00:11:07,041
I AM.

185
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:09,417
SO THIS IS ABOUT PUTTING
MY IDENTITY ON THE PAGE, RIGHT?

186
00:11:26,166 --> 00:11:32,125
[GRUNTING...]

187
00:11:35,250 --> 00:11:39,250
LANDSCAPE PAINTING TEACHES
A WARRIOR TO HOLD THE LAY OF
THE LAND IN HIS MIND.

188
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,667
[GRUNTING]

189
00:11:42,709 --> 00:11:46,250
IN BATTLE,
YOU ONLY HAVE AN INSTANT
TO TAKE EVERYTHING IN.

190
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:54,959
NOW, PAINT IT.

191
00:11:57,709 --> 00:11:58,917
AND NO PEEKING.

192
00:12:14,667 --> 00:12:17,667
Sokka: I'M FINISHED.

193
00:12:17,709 --> 00:12:19,792
YOU ADDED A RAINBOW.

194
00:12:19,834 --> 00:12:22,667
IS THAT OK?

195
00:12:22,709 --> 00:12:24,834
[SIGHING]

196
00:12:28,041 --> 00:12:29,875
[GRUNTING]

197
00:12:29,917 --> 00:12:31,917
Piandao: SOKKA.

198
00:12:31,959 --> 00:12:33,834
[GRUNTING]

199
00:12:33,875 --> 00:12:37,792
CONCENTRATE ON
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

200
00:12:37,834 --> 00:12:41,500
ROCK GARDENING
TEACHES THE WARRIOR
TO MANIPULATE HIS SURROUNDINGS

201
00:12:41,542 --> 00:12:44,125
AND USE THEM TO HIS ADVANTAGE.

202
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:48,041
HM, MANIPULATE THEM
TO MY ADVANTAGE.

203
00:12:48,542 --> 00:12:51,709
OH.

204
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:57,250
[GRUNTING...]

205
00:13:03,917 --> 00:13:06,458
AH.

206
00:13:08,166 --> 00:13:10,709
[GASPING]

207
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:13,041
HEY, WOULD YOU MIND GRABBING
A COLD DRINK FOR ME?

208
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:14,166
[GASPING]

209
00:13:14,208 --> 00:13:16,417
I'LL TAKE A SLICE OF LEMON
IN MINE, PLEASE.

210
00:13:16,458 --> 00:13:18,166
[SIGHING]

211
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:56,083
WHAT'S GOING ON IN THERE?

212
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:03,041
CRAZY OLD MAN.

213
00:14:09,792 --> 00:14:11,875
Katara: SO WHERE ARE
WE GOING NEXT?

214
00:14:11,917 --> 00:14:14,291
WE'RE STARTING FROM HERE.

215
00:14:14,333 --> 00:14:16,667
NO, WE'RE OVER ON THIS ISLAND.

216
00:14:16,709 --> 00:14:19,542
YOU NOODLE-BRAINS DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

217
00:14:19,583 --> 00:14:20,667
I MISS SOKKA.

218
00:14:20,709 --> 00:14:23,291
OOH, I GOT ONE.

219
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:26,375
IF YOU MISS HIM SO MUCH,
WHY DON'T YOU MARRY HIM?

220
00:14:34,458 --> 00:14:36,250
Piandao: YOU'VE HAD A GOOD
FIRST DAY OF TRAINING.

221
00:14:36,291 --> 00:14:38,291
I HAVE?

222
00:14:38,333 --> 00:14:40,417
BUT I THOUGHT I MESSED UP
EVERY SINGLE THING WE WORKED ON.

223
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:44,083
YOU MESSED THINGS UP
IN A VERY SPECIAL WAY.

224
00:14:44,125 --> 00:14:46,583
YOU ARE READY FOR A REAL SWORD.

225
00:14:46,625 --> 00:14:47,667
[GASPING]

226
00:14:47,709 --> 00:14:48,834
ARE YOU GIVING ME ONE OF YOURS?

227
00:14:48,875 --> 00:14:49,709
NO.

228
00:14:49,750 --> 00:14:51,125
[GROANING]

229
00:14:51,166 --> 00:14:54,625
YOUR SWORD MUST BE
AN EXTENSION OF YOURSELF

230
00:14:54,667 --> 00:14:58,291
SO TOMORROW, YOU WILL MAKE
YOUR OWN SWORD.

231
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:11,542
CHOOSING THE CORRECT MATERIAL
IS THE MOST IMPORTANT STEP
IN CRAFTING A SWORD.

232
00:15:11,583 --> 00:15:14,291
YOU MUST TRUST YOUR STEEL
WITH YOUR LIFE.

233
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:15,083
CHOOSE CAREFULLY.

234
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:20,709
[GRUNTING]

235
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:25,166
MASTER, WOULD IT BE POSSIBLE
FOR ME TO LEAVE AND BRING BACK
A SPECIAL MATERIAL FOR MY SWORD?

236
00:15:27,125 --> 00:15:28,750
I WOULDN'T HAVE IT
ANY OTHER WAY.

237
00:15:32,792 --> 00:15:33,500
SOKKA'S COMING.

238
00:15:33,542 --> 00:15:34,208
[GASPING]

239
00:15:34,250 --> 00:15:35,000
HEY, GUYS.

240
00:15:35,041 --> 00:15:36,000
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

241
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:36,917
Aang: SOKKA?

242
00:15:36,959 --> 00:15:37,834
Toph: YOU'RE BACK.

243
00:15:37,875 --> 00:15:39,667
WE MISSED YOU SO MUCH.

244
00:15:39,709 --> 00:15:41,208
SAY SOMETHING FUNNY.

245
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:42,542
FUNNY HOW?

246
00:15:42,583 --> 00:15:45,542
[LAUGHING]

247
00:15:45,583 --> 00:15:46,959
WHAT'S THEIR DEAL?

248
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,542
I DON'T KNOW.

249
00:15:48,583 --> 00:15:50,041
THEY MISSED YOU OR SOMETHING.

250
00:15:50,083 --> 00:15:51,375
I DIDN'T CARE.

251
00:15:51,417 --> 00:15:52,500
THANKS.

252
00:15:52,542 --> 00:15:54,166
THAT WARMS MY HEART.

253
00:15:54,208 --> 00:15:55,417
ANYWAY, I NEED SOME HELP.

254
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:16,959
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

255
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:33,000
WHO'S THIS?

256
00:16:33,041 --> 00:16:35,000
OH, THESE ARE MY FRIENDS.

257
00:16:35,041 --> 00:16:38,542
JUST OTHER GOOD
FIRE NATION FOLKS.

258
00:16:38,583 --> 00:16:41,333
DO YOU THINK WE CAN MAKE
A SWORD OUT OF A METEORITE?

259
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:44,792
WE'LL MAKE A SWORD UNLIKE
ANY OTHER IN THE WORLD.

260
00:17:43,417 --> 00:17:47,834
SOKKA, WHEN YOU FIRST ARRIVED,
YOU WERE SO UNSURE.

261
00:17:47,875 --> 00:17:50,208
YOU EVEN SEEMED
DOWN ON YOURSELF.

262
00:17:50,250 --> 00:17:52,875
BUT I SAW SOMETHING
IN YOU RIGHT AWAY.

263
00:17:52,917 --> 00:17:57,542
I SAW A HEART AS STRONG AS
A LION TURTLE, AND TWICE AS BIG

264
00:17:57,583 --> 00:18:02,125
AND AS WE TRAINED, IT WASN'T
YOUR SKILLS THAT IMPRESSED ME.

265
00:18:02,166 --> 00:18:05,542
NO, IT CERTAINLY
WASN'T YOUR SKILLS.

266
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:10,500
YOU SHOWED SOMETHING
BEYOND THAT.

267
00:18:10,542 --> 00:18:15,875
CREATIVITY, VERSATILITY,
INTELLIGENCE.

268
00:18:15,917 --> 00:18:18,417
THESE ARE THE TRAITS
THAT DEFINE A GREAT SWORDSMAN

269
00:18:18,458 --> 00:18:22,291
AND THESE ARE THE TRAITS
THAT DEFINE YOU.

270
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:27,041
YOU TOLD ME YOU DIDN'T KNOW
IF YOU WERE WORTHY

271
00:18:27,083 --> 00:18:32,542
BUT I BELIEVE THAT YOU
ARE MORE WORTHY THAN ANY MAN
I HAVE EVER TRAINED.

272
00:18:35,875 --> 00:18:37,625
I'M SORRY, MASTER.

273
00:18:37,667 --> 00:18:38,542
YOU'RE WRONG.

274
00:18:38,583 --> 00:18:40,875
I AM NOT WORTHY.

275
00:18:40,917 --> 00:18:42,959
I'M NOT WHO YOU THINK I AM.

276
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,166
I'M NOT FROM THE FIRE NATION.

277
00:18:44,208 --> 00:18:46,417
I'M FROM THE SOUTHERN
WATER TRIBE.

278
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:48,875
I LIED SO THAT I COULD
LEARN SWORDSMANSHIP FROM YOU.

279
00:18:50,041 --> 00:18:50,917
I'M SORRY.

280
00:18:50,959 --> 00:18:54,250
I'M SORRY, TOO.

281
00:18:54,291 --> 00:18:57,166
[GASPING]

282
00:18:57,208 --> 00:19:01,333
NO, THIS IS MY FIGHT, ALONE.

283
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,834
YOU USED TO BE
THE PRIDE OF THE FIRE NATION.

284
00:19:08,875 --> 00:19:11,709
OUR TOP GENERAL,
THE DRAGON OF THE WEST.

285
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:15,792
NOW, LOOK AT YOU.

286
00:19:15,834 --> 00:19:16,875
LOOK WHAT YOU'VE BECOME.

287
00:19:28,709 --> 00:19:29,542
[GRUNTING]

288
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:58,959
[GRUNTING...]

289
00:20:10,041 --> 00:20:11,792
Piandao: EXCELLENT.

290
00:20:11,834 --> 00:20:14,709
USING YOUR SUPERIOR AGILITY
AGAINST AN OLDER OPPONENT.

291
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:15,959
SMART.

292
00:20:20,333 --> 00:20:23,750
[GRUNTING...]

293
00:20:32,583 --> 00:20:34,041
Piandao: GOOD USE OF TERRAIN.

294
00:20:34,083 --> 00:20:35,125
FIGHTING FROM THE HIGH GROUND.

295
00:20:40,667 --> 00:20:41,792
[GRUNTING]

296
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:03,667
YES, USE YOUR SURROUNDINGS.

297
00:21:03,709 --> 00:21:05,375
MAKE THEM FIGHT FOR YOU.

298
00:21:05,417 --> 00:21:08,333
[SCREAMING]

299
00:21:08,375 --> 00:21:11,291
[PANTING]

300
00:21:15,542 --> 00:21:16,583
[GRUNTING]

301
00:21:19,834 --> 00:21:21,375
[COUGHING]

302
00:21:21,417 --> 00:21:24,250
VERY RESOURCEFUL.

303
00:21:53,792 --> 00:21:55,041
EXCELLENT WORK, SOKKA.

304
00:22:03,583 --> 00:22:06,959
I THINK I'M A LITTLE OLD
TO BE FIGHTING THE AVATAR.

305
00:22:08,417 --> 00:22:09,250
HOW DID YOU KNOW?

306
00:22:09,291 --> 00:22:11,750
OH, I'VE BEEN AROUND A WHILE.

307
00:22:11,792 --> 00:22:13,625
YOU PICK THINGS UP.

308
00:22:13,667 --> 00:22:15,834
OF COURSE, I KNEW
FROM THE BEGINNING THAT SOKKA
WAS WATER TRIBE.

309
00:22:15,875 --> 00:22:19,875
YOU MIGHT WANT TO THINK OF
A BETTER FIRE NATION COVER NAME.

310
00:22:20,667 --> 00:22:21,959
TRY "LEE."

311
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,709
THERE'S A MILLION LEES.

312
00:22:23,750 --> 00:22:26,875
BUT WHY WOULD YOU AGREE
TO TRAIN SOMEONE
FROM THE WATER TRIBE?

313
00:22:26,917 --> 00:22:30,250
THE WAY OF THE SWORD DOESN'T
BELONG TO ANY ONE NATION.

314
00:22:30,291 --> 00:22:32,542
KNOWLEDGE OF THE ARTS
BELONGS TO US ALL.

315
00:22:36,458 --> 00:22:41,875
SOKKA, YOU MUST CONTINUE
YOUR TRAINING ON YOUR OWN.

316
00:22:41,917 --> 00:22:45,542
IF YOU STAY ON THIS PATH,
I KNOW THAT ONE DAY

317
00:22:45,583 --> 00:22:48,583
YOU WILL BECOME AN EVEN
GREATER MASTER THAN I AM.

318
00:22:57,458 --> 00:22:59,542
- WAIT.

319
00:22:59,583 --> 00:23:04,041
THE MASTER WANTED YOU
TO HAVE THIS, AS SOMETHING
TO REMEMBER HIM BY.

320
00:23:11,542 --> 00:23:12,917
IT'S A PAI SHO TILE.

321
00:23:12,959 --> 00:23:14,500
Aang: THE WHITE LOTUS.

322
00:23:14,542 --> 00:23:15,375
HM.

323
00:23:15,417 --> 00:23:16,417
Katara: WHAT DOES IT MEAN?

324
00:23:16,458 --> 00:23:17,500
I HAVE NO IDEA.

325
00:23:20,917 --> 00:23:22,917
OOH, THAT REMINDS ME.

326
00:23:22,959 --> 00:23:24,625
TOPH, I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT LIKE THIS

327
00:23:24,667 --> 00:23:27,375
SINCE YOU'VE PROBABLY
NEVER HAD A CHANCE
TO BEND SPACE EARTH BEFORE.

328
00:23:27,417 --> 00:23:29,500
SWEET.

329
00:23:29,542 --> 00:23:32,333
CHECK THIS OUT.

330
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:38,166
YOU KNOW, I DON'T THINK THERE'S
SUCH A THING AS "SPACE EARTH."

331
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:40,875
IF IT'S FROM SPACE,
THEN IT'S NOT REALLY EARTH.

332
00:23:40,917 --> 00:23:42,417
Sokka: MUST YOU RUIN EVERYTHING?

333
00:23:42,458 --> 00:23:44,000
Katara: I CAN'T BELIEVE
I MISSED YOU.

334
00:23:52,583 --> 00:23:58,375
♪
